sVnews
p4
VVocalist Meeta Pandit, young torch bearer of the Gwalior gharana of Hindustani music, has just returned to India after a successful tour of Europe, where she performed as part of Namaste India in France, as well as venues in Austria, not to mention the &#8220;Amsterdam Baithak&#8221;. As is the practice with the Indian Council for Cultural Relations on the return of artistes sponsored by it on cultural tours, Meeta performs a concert of Hindustani music this Friday evening at ICCR's Azad Bhawan auditorium, 6 to 7 p.m.She was accompanied on the tour by Shailendra Mishra (tabla), Bharat Bhushan Goswami (sarangi), Manmohan Nayak (pakhawaj) and Abha Pandit (tanpura). Most of these artistes will be performing with her at Azad Bhawan this evening.
